<paragraph blockId="3.[159,762,1749,1949]" lastBlockId="3.[826,1429,311,405]" pageId="3" pageNumber="21">
Diagnosis — As of 
<bibRefCitation author="Shaw M. D. &amp; Seeman O. D." box="[393,694,1749,1773]" pageId="3" pageNumber="21" pagination="43 - 55" refId="ref4924" refString="Shaw M. D., Seeman O. D. 2009 - Two new species of Myrmozercon (Acari: Laelapidae) from Australian ants (Hymenoptera: Formicidae) - Zootaxa, 2025: 43 - 55." type="journal article" year="2009">Shaw and Seeman (2009)</bibRefCitation>
, with amendment by 
<bibRefCitation author="Joharchi O. &amp; Moradi M." box="[351,683,1784,1808]" pageId="3" pageNumber="21" pagination="244 - 254" refId="ref4656" refString="Joharchi O., Moradi M. 2013 - Review of the genus Myrmozercon Berlese (Acari: Laelapidae), with description of two new species from Iran - Zootaxa, 3686 (2): 244 - 254." type="journal article" year="2013">Joharchi and Moradi (2013)</bibRefCitation>
based on 
<taxonomicName authority="Joharchi, 2013" authorityName="Joharchi" authorityYear="2013" box="[196,613,1819,1843]" class="Arachnida" family="Laelapidae" genus="Myrmozercon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mesostigmata" pageId="3" pageNumber="21" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="michaeli">
<emphasis box="[196,442,1819,1843]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="21">Myrmozercon michaeli</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Joharchi O. &amp; Moradi M." box="[449,613,1819,1843]" pageId="3" pageNumber="21" pagination="244 - 254" refId="ref4656" refString="Joharchi O., Moradi M. 2013 - Review of the genus Myrmozercon Berlese (Acari: Laelapidae), with description of two new species from Iran - Zootaxa, 3686 (2): 244 - 254." type="journal article" year="2013">Joharchi, 2013</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
(seven rows of deutosternal denticles instead of&gt; 7) and the following modification based on the redescription of the 
<typeStatus box="[202,254,1925,1949]" pageId="3" pageNumber="21">type</typeStatus>
species: fixed digit of chelicerae reduced to absent; deutosternal groove with 5-16 rows of numerous denticles, or each row comprising one large denticle.
</paragraph>
